1
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:23,900
Sons of a duck...

2
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:04,867
Boss, this is your end!

3
00:01:29,067 --> 00:01:32,367
No matter what hellhole
you hide in,

4
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,967
I'll hunt you down.

5
00:01:38,267 --> 00:01:40,133
<i>- Sons of a duck.
- Sons of a duck!</i>

6
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:44,500
- Boss!
- Boss!

7
00:01:44,633 --> 00:01:46,767
- Boss!
- Boss!

8
00:01:46,900 --> 00:01:56,867
Boss! Boss! Boss! Boss!

9
00:02:22,167 --> 00:02:24,833
Boss!

10
00:02:25,833 --> 00:02:27,133
Boss is really the best.

11
00:02:27,833 --> 00:02:28,767
Idol!

12
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:40,233
Freeze!

13
00:02:51,433 --> 00:02:52,800
Hands up!

14
00:02:58,267 --> 00:03:02,800
They say,
"Cinema is a mirror of life,

15
00:03:02,933 --> 00:03:05,833
a reflection of our society."

16
00:03:05,967 --> 00:03:12,967
You can understand a culture or
a nation through its movies.

17
00:03:13,667 --> 00:03:17,900
That's why it's a great honor

18
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:21,200
for me to have my films

19
00:03:21,367 --> 00:03:24,567
included in this exhibit.

20
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:26,567
Boss, can we ask you a question?

21
00:03:26,700 --> 00:03:27,733
What is it?

22
00:03:27,867 --> 00:03:30,733
I just want to confirm
if the rumors are true,

23
00:03:30,867 --> 00:03:35,267
that you're entering
the world of politics?

24
00:03:39,233 --> 00:03:40,800
Oh...

25
00:03:45,533 --> 00:03:47,000
Yes.

26
00:03:47,467 --> 00:03:49,467
The rumors are true.

27
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:53,633
I'm running
for Mayor of Calabari!

28
00:04:00,867 --> 00:04:02,367
Why are we even here?

29
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:03,700
Don't tell me you believe

30
00:04:03,833 --> 00:04:05,800
that museum director's hunch

31
00:04:05,933 --> 00:04:08,633
that there's going to be
a robbery tonight.

32
00:04:09,167 --> 00:04:11,700
Everything starts with a hunch,
right?

33
00:04:12,667 --> 00:04:13,800
A hunch?

34
00:04:13,933 --> 00:04:15,400
We're just wasting
our time here.

35
00:04:15,533 --> 00:04:17,333
This place is so secure.

36
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:18,733
It has high ceilings.

37
00:04:19,867 --> 00:04:22,433
No one's going to break in here.

38
00:04:32,933 --> 00:04:34,500
It's safe.

39
00:04:35,567 --> 00:04:37,300
But, Bok, I've got a feeling

40
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:40,300
something bad
is going down tonight.

41
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:43,733
Okay, okay.

42
00:04:43,867 --> 00:04:45,467
What's your plan?

43
00:04:56,633 --> 00:04:58,067
You go ahead to the museum.

44
00:04:59,000 --> 00:04:59,833
I'll follow you.

45
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:01,867
- Yes, Boss.
- Let's go.

46
00:05:06,133 --> 00:05:08,200
- Ma'am, here's your coffee.
- Thank you.

47
00:05:09,833 --> 00:05:11,600
Ma'am, patrolling's boring

48
00:05:11,733 --> 00:05:13,867
especially when nothing's
happening.

49
00:05:14,933 --> 00:05:17,233
Quiet's good though.

50
00:05:18,367 --> 00:05:20,833
How's your transfer request

51
00:05:20,967 --> 00:05:23,233
to the investigation unit going?

52
00:05:24,367 --> 00:05:25,800
Well...

53
00:05:25,933 --> 00:05:28,700
Chief said it's already been
passed to HQ...

54
00:05:30,900 --> 00:05:33,533
but it's been 6 months.

55
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:37,267
Oh my, that's the same thing
he said to me.

56
00:05:37,667 --> 00:05:38,967
It took years of follow-ups

57
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:42,133
but it's always
"Try again next time."

58
00:05:42,267 --> 00:05:44,867
Until I got tired and
started a family.

59
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,300
Ma'am, you know how badly I want

60
00:05:46,433 --> 00:05:48,400
to become an investigator,
right?

61
00:05:48,533 --> 00:05:51,167
I also promised that
to my mother.

62
00:05:51,867 --> 00:05:55,467
So, are you saying
I should give up too?

63
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:57,767
It's not like that, Bobby.

64
00:05:58,833 --> 00:06:01,133
What I am trying to say is,

65
00:06:01,267 --> 00:06:04,133
you just need to manage
your expectations.

66
00:06:04,267 --> 00:06:05,800
Although, it's hard to admit...

67
00:06:05,933 --> 00:06:10,900
that it's much difficult for
police women like us.

68
00:06:11,067 --> 00:06:12,900
But I promise...

69
00:06:13,033 --> 00:06:16,467
I'll be the first to be happy
when you're promoted.

70
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:20,367
Police Inspector Bobby Enriquez.

71
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:30,533
Let's go, let's go!

72
00:06:38,900 --> 00:06:42,167
Take everything you can sell,
okay?

73
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:55,700
See? I knew my hunch was right.

74
00:07:03,700 --> 00:07:05,067
That was gunfire, Ma'am.

75
00:07:06,033 --> 00:07:08,067
This looks like it
came from a museum.

76
00:07:09,733 --> 00:07:12,133
Looks like our night
just got interesting.

77
00:07:20,567 --> 00:07:22,300
Call for backup!

78
00:08:10,133 --> 00:08:11,667
Hey! That's expensive!

79
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:24,700
I said that's expensive!

80
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:43,333
Why did you throw it?

81
00:08:44,267 --> 00:08:45,100
I thought this was expensive.

82
00:08:46,533 --> 00:08:47,733
Good thing, you reminded me.

83
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:53,200
What? Is it painful?

84
00:08:53,333 --> 00:08:54,733
Yes, yes.

85
00:08:55,833 --> 00:08:56,933
What?

86
00:08:57,067 --> 00:08:58,567
You can't take me!

87
00:08:58,700 --> 00:09:00,300
What?

88
00:09:07,033 --> 00:09:08,333
- Come on, let's hurry.
- Let's go.

89
00:09:15,133 --> 00:09:17,367
Stop right there!
Put your hands up!

90
00:09:20,467 --> 00:09:21,733
You're alone?

91
00:09:21,867 --> 00:09:23,167
There's three of us!

92
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:24,900
And you're a woman!

93
00:09:26,667 --> 00:09:28,367
You're crazy.

94
00:09:47,733 --> 00:09:48,833
I'm sorry.

95
00:10:21,367 --> 00:10:22,533
Come on, try it!

96
00:10:42,633 --> 00:10:45,900
Ouch!

97
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:01,633
I'm sorry, Bok.

98
00:11:01,767 --> 00:11:03,267
I thought you were one of them.

99
00:11:03,767 --> 00:11:05,500
Our hunch were right.

100
00:11:06,767 --> 00:11:08,533
There are people
who will break in.

101
00:11:09,667 --> 00:11:13,000
Alpha to all units,
report your status.

102
00:11:17,700 --> 00:11:21,133
Sir, all your companion
are still out.

103
00:11:22,900 --> 00:11:25,000
This is Lieutenant
Antonio Conde.

104
00:11:25,133 --> 00:11:26,067
Who is this?

105
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:28,700
Oh, Sir, it's
Sergeant Enriquez.

106
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:30,533
<i> We heard the shots,</i>

107
00:11:30,667 --> 00:11:32,467
<i> so we came to assist.</i>

108
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:34,367
<i>We thought
you might need backup.</i>

109
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:37,900
Thanks, but we've got this.

110
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:41,100
Arrogant.

111
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:46,800
<i>Sir, I'll follow one of them,
he might escape.</i>

112
00:11:49,367 --> 00:11:50,600
Bok, I'll leave this to you!

113
00:11:51,533 --> 00:11:52,933
Okay, okay.

114
00:11:56,567 --> 00:11:57,700
You're all shameless, what?

115
00:12:02,267 --> 00:12:03,800
Freeze!

116
00:12:06,033 --> 00:12:07,733
Put your hands up!

117
00:13:27,967 --> 00:13:29,033
We're awesome, Sir.

118
00:13:29,167 --> 00:13:30,400
We still would've caught them

119
00:13:30,533 --> 00:13:32,233
even if you didn't come.

120
00:13:36,667 --> 00:13:38,433
Arrogant.

121
00:13:55,033 --> 00:13:57,167
Congratulations,
Lieutenant Conde.

122
00:13:57,633 --> 00:13:58,900
Based on the initial report,

123
00:13:59,033 --> 00:14:01,467
all museum items
were accounted for,

124
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:04,467
all the theives were
apprehended,

125
00:14:05,033 --> 00:14:06,800
and nothing was stolen
in the museum.

126
00:14:06,933 --> 00:14:09,033
Great job, Lieutenant Conde.

127
00:14:09,167 --> 00:14:11,167
- Thank you, Sir.
- Great job.

128
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:19,833
Oh, Manalo, I heard...

129
00:14:19,967 --> 00:14:21,667
you and your godchild, Enriquez,

130
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:24,000
meddle in Station 12's
operation?

131
00:14:24,133 --> 00:14:25,100
What do you mean meddle?

132
00:14:25,233 --> 00:14:26,967
Don't you know?

133
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:29,367
Half of those arrests

134
00:14:29,533 --> 00:14:33,400
were because
of Sergeant Enriquez.

135
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:38,433
That's what Major Flores
from Station 12 told me too.

136
00:14:39,133 --> 00:14:40,100
Sit down.

137
00:14:41,067 --> 00:14:42,933
Good job, Sergeant Enriquez.

138
00:14:43,067 --> 00:14:45,700
Looks like your transfer to the
Investigation Group

139
00:14:45,833 --> 00:14:48,033
might happen sooner
than you think.

140
00:14:48,167 --> 00:14:49,133
Thank you, Sir.

141
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,200
At least mine has...

142
00:15:00,333 --> 00:15:01,200
It's all good.

143
00:15:01,900 --> 00:15:02,533
Thank you.

144
00:15:03,333 --> 00:15:04,500
Bobby!

145
00:15:05,467 --> 00:15:06,600
Let me take you home.

146
00:15:06,733 --> 00:15:08,667
Oh, Ma'am Bobby, don't listen
to that short one.

147
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:09,667
I'll take you home.

148
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:10,767
You see that?

149
00:15:10,900 --> 00:15:11,867
You know what? You've been
annoying since earlier.

150
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:13,833
You're getting real cocky.
What do you want, huh?

151
00:15:13,967 --> 00:15:15,367
- Oh, why?
- You, what do you want?

152
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:17,367
Both of you, cut it out!

153
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:18,767
My house is just nearby.

154
00:15:18,900 --> 00:15:20,233
I can walk home alone.

155
00:15:20,367 --> 00:15:22,500
- I said I'll take her.
- You guys are unbelievable.

156
00:15:22,633 --> 00:15:25,100
- Unbelievable.
- Hey, Ma'am Bobby...

157
00:15:25,233 --> 00:15:26,333
maybe...

158
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:28,200
maybe I really should be
the one to take you home?

159
00:15:28,333 --> 00:15:29,367
Don't mind him.

160
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:33,467
Oh, Ma'am Bobby, aren't you
already in your 30's?

161
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,100
Yes, Ma'am Bobby.

162
00:15:35,267 --> 00:15:36,700
When are you getting married?

163
00:15:38,700 --> 00:15:40,000
You know what?
I only have one answer

164
00:15:40,133 --> 00:15:41,967
to questions like that, okay?

165
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:43,467
Listen closely.

166
00:15:44,433 --> 00:15:46,400
I'll only get married

167
00:15:46,533 --> 00:15:48,233
when the Lord
takes away everyone

168
00:15:48,367 --> 00:15:49,600
asking me that question.

169
00:15:49,733 --> 00:15:50,400
What?

170
00:15:51,933 --> 00:15:53,467
That's harsh.
You want Lord to take them.

171
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:54,500
- Hey, hey, hey!
- You are too much.

172
00:15:54,633 --> 00:15:56,433
What are you doing
to my granddaughter?

173
00:15:56,567 --> 00:15:57,500
I'm sorry, Village Chief.

174
00:15:57,633 --> 00:15:59,200
Don't fight over her
out here in the street.

175
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:02,667
If you wanna court her,
go to the house.

176
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:04,167
Come on, now.

177
00:16:04,300 --> 00:16:05,500
I'll go up and court you, okay?

178
00:16:05,633 --> 00:16:06,400
- Village Chief
- I'll go first.

179
00:16:06,533 --> 00:16:08,933
Oh, make sure
you all go home early.

180
00:16:09,100 --> 00:16:09,667
Yes, Ma'am.

181
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:11,433
Stop drinking too much.

182
00:16:12,567 --> 00:16:15,233
Hey, dear, aren't you already in
your 30's?

183
00:16:15,367 --> 00:16:16,333
Why?

184
00:16:16,467 --> 00:16:17,967
Don't you wanna get married yet?

185
00:16:18,100 --> 00:16:19,933
Village Chief!

186
00:16:20,067 --> 00:16:21,600
We already know
the answer to that one.

187
00:16:21,733 --> 00:16:24,233
Village Chief, Bobby only has
one answer to that.

188
00:16:24,367 --> 00:16:26,500
- Bobby will only get married
- Bobby will only get married

189
00:16:26,633 --> 00:16:27,500
- when...
- when...

190
00:16:27,633 --> 00:16:28,933
Go ahead, I dare you
to finish that sentence.

191
00:16:29,067 --> 00:16:30,500
When you shake off your clothes?

192
00:16:30,633 --> 00:16:32,233
- I'll shake it off...
- We're not even sure.

193
00:16:32,367 --> 00:16:33,633
- I'm not even sure myself.
- It's your fault.

194
00:16:33,767 --> 00:16:35,300
- You're not sure.
- Go ahead.

195
00:16:35,433 --> 00:16:37,233
- Sorry, Village Chief.
- All right.

196
00:16:37,367 --> 00:16:38,733
That's enough from those two.

197
00:16:38,867 --> 00:16:39,967
You know, they're fishy.

198
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:41,567
I don't trust them.

199
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:44,233
Let them be.

200
00:16:44,900 --> 00:16:46,600
- Oh, it's Sir Tonyo!
- What?

201
00:16:46,733 --> 00:16:48,367
- Hi, Sir Tonyo!
- Hey!

202
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:50,000
Boss Tonyo!

203
00:16:52,667 --> 00:16:54,533
Boss Tonyo, have a shot!

204
00:16:54,667 --> 00:16:56,133
Have a shot, just one!

205
00:16:57,167 --> 00:16:59,000
You guys look like
you've had a lot.

206
00:16:59,133 --> 00:17:00,133
Not really, Boss.

207
00:17:00,267 --> 00:17:01,533
Just enough to get me to sleep.

208
00:17:01,667 --> 00:17:02,767
Get you to sleep?

209
00:17:02,900 --> 00:17:04,500
Apple and Peach here already
look tipsy.

210
00:17:04,633 --> 00:17:06,633
- Not yet, Sir Tonyo.
- Not yet?

211
00:17:06,767 --> 00:17:08,933
Those two are
all about the snacks.

212
00:17:09,067 --> 00:17:10,567
I'm the one doing
all the drinking.

213
00:17:11,233 --> 00:17:14,367
Actually, Sir Tonyo,
we're heading out to buy more.

214
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:17,367
Can we hitch a ride with you?

215
00:17:17,533 --> 00:17:18,867
You both wanna ride with me?

216
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:19,867
You two?

217
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:23,200
Yes, one in front, one in back.

218
00:17:23,700 --> 00:17:26,200
- Come on, please, Sir Tonyo.
- Sir Tonyo.

219
00:17:26,333 --> 00:17:27,267
- Just this once.
- Boss Tonyo and I

220
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:28,233
will have another drink.

221
00:17:28,367 --> 00:17:29,867
- You can bother him later.
- Come on.

222
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:30,900
Just this once.

223
00:17:31,033 --> 00:17:32,567
I'll grant the request
of these two.

224
00:17:33,933 --> 00:17:35,367
Bye, Beteng!

225
00:17:37,100 --> 00:17:38,633
Tonyo!

226
00:17:38,767 --> 00:17:40,100
Where are you going?

227
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:45,133
Lara...

228
00:17:45,267 --> 00:17:46,500
Nowhere.

229
00:17:46,633 --> 00:17:48,067
I'm going home.

230
00:17:56,100 --> 00:17:58,567
<i>So? Did you like
the movie we watched?</i>

231
00:17:58,700 --> 00:18:00,133
<i> Yes!</i>

232
00:18:00,267 --> 00:18:03,400
<i>Boss is really awesome
in fighting.</i>

233
00:18:05,467 --> 00:18:07,400
<i> Oh, that's amazing!</i>

234
00:18:08,033 --> 00:18:11,267
<i>When I grow up,
I want to be just like him.</i>

235
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:12,833
<i> What? You want to be an actor?</i>

236
00:18:12,967 --> 00:18:16,000
<i> Not an actor, Mommy.</i>

237
00:18:16,133 --> 00:18:20,300
<i>I want to be a cop and a great
investigator</i>

238
00:18:20,433 --> 00:18:22,567
<i> like in Boss' movie.</i>

239
00:18:22,733 --> 00:18:25,967
<i> Oh, I like that, Dear.</i>

240
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:28,967
<i>I'll have a daugther who is a
police officer.</i>

241
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:31,433
<i> Come give your mom a hug.</i>

242
00:18:31,567 --> 00:18:32,400
<i> You're getting so big.</i>

243
00:18:32,533 --> 00:18:34,133
<i> Oh, oh, oh, oh!</i>

244
00:18:34,267 --> 00:18:35,633
<i>- Miss...
- Mommy...</i>

245
00:18:35,767 --> 00:18:37,100
<i> Give me your bag.</i>

246
00:18:38,933 --> 00:18:40,167
<i>- Stay back! Stay back!
- Mommy!</i>

247
00:18:40,300 --> 00:18:41,067
<i> Come closer, stay close!</i>

248
00:18:41,733 --> 00:18:43,500
<i> Mommy!</i>

249
00:18:43,633 --> 00:18:46,433
<i> Let go of my mother!</i>

250
00:18:49,167 --> 00:18:51,733
<i> Mommy! Mommy!</i>

251
00:18:51,867 --> 00:18:52,800
<i> Mommy!</i>

252
00:18:52,933 --> 00:18:54,400
<i> Help!</i>

253
00:18:54,533 --> 00:18:56,800
<i> Help us!</i>

254
00:19:03,967 --> 00:19:05,367
Dear...

255
00:19:06,333 --> 00:19:08,867
Thinking of your mom again?

256
00:19:10,167 --> 00:19:11,467
Of course, Grandmother.

257
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:14,600
I always think about her
and remember her.

258
00:19:14,733 --> 00:19:18,633
Then why don't you tell her
about your promotion?

259
00:19:18,767 --> 00:19:20,833
She'd be so happy.

260
00:19:20,967 --> 00:19:23,967
She'd be so proud of you.

261
00:19:31,900 --> 00:19:34,200
I heard your men got caught.

262
00:19:34,333 --> 00:19:36,267
Even the jewelries
were recovered.

263
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,100
Yes, Boss.

264
00:19:38,233 --> 00:19:39,533
I'm sorry.

265
00:19:39,667 --> 00:19:41,400
That's a big problem.

266
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:42,967
They might snitch on you.

267
00:19:46,433 --> 00:19:47,600
That would not to happen, Boss.

268
00:19:47,733 --> 00:19:49,567
Those guys are quiet.

269
00:19:49,700 --> 00:19:50,567
Just make sure of it.

270
00:19:51,633 --> 00:19:55,800
What about the special package
boss asked for?

271
00:20:03,367 --> 00:20:06,167
And the robbery was a success.

272
00:20:06,300 --> 00:20:07,900
Good job.

273
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,667
Are you mad?

274
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:14,933
Aren't you supposed to be
a good investigator?

275
00:20:15,067 --> 00:20:16,700
What do you think?

276
00:20:23,767 --> 00:20:25,600
Lara...

277
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:28,367
is it my fault...

278
00:20:30,067 --> 00:20:32,567
that women are drawn to me?

279
00:20:32,700 --> 00:20:36,633
Oh, women are drwan to you?

280
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:38,800
Then why don't you
push them away?

281
00:20:39,333 --> 00:20:40,333
Well, it looks like

282
00:20:40,467 --> 00:20:42,233
you're going to give them a ride
on your motorcycle,

283
00:20:42,367 --> 00:20:43,667
right, Tonyo?

284
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:46,167
They were just asking
for a favor.

285
00:20:46,300 --> 00:20:47,167
A favor?

286
00:20:47,300 --> 00:20:49,433
It will make me look bad
if I refuse, right?

287
00:20:49,567 --> 00:20:52,433
Oh, Tonyo, you make a lot of
excuses.

288
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:05,533
I'm sorry, Love.

289
00:21:07,900 --> 00:21:10,567
You know I won't replace you
for anyone.

290
00:21:11,300 --> 00:21:13,633
No matter who approaches me,

291
00:21:14,167 --> 00:21:16,133
I can't replace you for anyone.

292
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:19,567
Even if it's Jennylyn Mercado.

293
00:21:19,700 --> 00:21:21,500
You're really crazy.

294
00:21:22,567 --> 00:21:26,300
Well, if you think about it,
I have no right to do that.

295
00:21:26,700 --> 00:21:28,667
We're not married yet.

296
00:21:30,167 --> 00:21:32,467
So you can go to your girls.

297
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:34,533
Love, hey...

298
00:21:34,667 --> 00:21:36,933
Don't give me away.

299
00:21:38,100 --> 00:21:41,633
My life will lose direction
if you're gone.

300
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:43,533
You're full of drama.

301
00:21:43,667 --> 00:21:45,400
That's not drama.

302
00:21:46,067 --> 00:21:47,533
That's true.

303
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:51,633
I don't know if I can handle it

304
00:21:51,767 --> 00:21:53,967
if you're gone.

305
00:21:54,767 --> 00:21:56,767
Well, don't worry

306
00:21:56,900 --> 00:21:58,967
because I won't be gone...

307
00:21:59,633 --> 00:22:01,667
because I'll watch over you.

308
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:05,933
If I catch you flirting with
someone else again,

309
00:22:06,067 --> 00:22:08,567
I'll cut that myself!

310
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:10,167
What?

311
00:22:11,533 --> 00:22:13,133
Your horn, Tonyo.

312
00:22:13,267 --> 00:22:14,500
What's with you?

313
00:22:14,633 --> 00:22:15,900
That Lieutenant Conde,
Grandmother,

314
00:22:16,067 --> 00:22:18,800
that's our head
of operations earlier.

315
00:22:18,933 --> 00:22:19,533
- Yes.
- You know, Grandmother,

316
00:22:19,667 --> 00:22:20,967
he's good.

317
00:22:21,100 --> 00:22:23,400
- What?
- But he's just arrogant.

318
00:22:23,533 --> 00:22:25,733
Well, who knows?

319
00:22:25,867 --> 00:22:27,133
Maybe he just don't want anyone

320
00:22:27,267 --> 00:22:29,300
interfering with their
operation.

321
00:22:29,433 --> 00:22:31,233
Well, aren't you the same?

322
00:22:31,367 --> 00:22:33,700
You don't like your toothbrush
being touched,

323
00:22:33,833 --> 00:22:35,067
right?

324
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:37,000
I'm just organized, Grandmother.

325
00:22:37,133 --> 00:22:39,233
- Really...
- And...

326
00:22:39,367 --> 00:22:40,867
Am I not your grandchild?

327
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:43,767
Why do you seem to be defending
other people?

328
00:22:43,900 --> 00:22:46,233
No.

329
00:22:46,367 --> 00:22:47,933
Of course not.

330
00:22:49,967 --> 00:22:51,600
Introduce me to him.

331
00:22:51,733 --> 00:22:55,033
Maybe that's what
we've been looking for.

332
00:22:55,167 --> 00:22:57,700
Come on! Oh, my. Hey,
Grandmother, what's with you?

333
00:22:57,833 --> 00:22:58,900
- Oh, why?
- I just said

334
00:22:59,033 --> 00:23:00,000
that I find him arrogant

335
00:23:00,133 --> 00:23:02,267
and then you want me to end up
with that person.

336
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:05,333
Who knows, maybe he's the one.

337
00:23:05,467 --> 00:23:08,300
Dear, there's just
the two of us.

338
00:23:08,433 --> 00:23:10,567
Oh, maybe he's the one.

339
00:23:10,700 --> 00:23:12,500
Well, if you want,

340
00:23:12,633 --> 00:23:14,933
I'll just find father
so there will be three of us.

341
00:23:15,067 --> 00:23:16,000
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

342
00:23:16,133 --> 00:23:17,767
Don't ever do that, okay?

343
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:20,067
Don't look for your father,

344
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:22,633
bacause your mother might
wake up from her grave.

345
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:25,133
Go ahead, and she'll haunt you.

346
00:23:25,267 --> 00:23:27,267
Your father is useless.
He's a bad guy.

347
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:29,367
Don't do that.

348
00:23:29,933 --> 00:23:31,567
That's what you're going to do.

349
00:23:31,700 --> 00:23:33,600
You're going to leave me too.

350
00:23:35,967 --> 00:23:37,833
Sorry, Grandmother.

351
00:23:39,100 --> 00:23:41,433
My point is

352
00:23:41,567 --> 00:23:42,767
you're just matching him with me

353
00:23:42,900 --> 00:23:44,533
we don't know that maybe,

354
00:23:44,667 --> 00:23:46,133
he has a wife.

355
00:23:46,267 --> 00:23:48,267
Aren't you an investigator?

356
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:53,500
Why don't you find out if
he's single or married, right?

357
00:23:59,233 --> 00:24:01,067
It seems like
he's not wearing a ring.

358
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:02,400
Oh!

359
00:24:02,533 --> 00:24:04,067
Oh, a bachelor!

360
00:24:04,200 --> 00:24:06,067
Dear, he's a bachelor!

361
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:07,533
- Grandmother!
- Come on!

362
00:24:07,667 --> 00:24:08,833
Come on, Grandmother?

363
00:24:08,967 --> 00:24:09,800
I don't care if

364
00:24:09,933 --> 00:24:11,500
he's single or married anymore.

365
00:24:11,633 --> 00:24:15,367
As long as I'm focused
on being an investigator

366
00:24:15,500 --> 00:24:16,533
like Boss.

367
00:24:16,667 --> 00:24:19,667
Well, you're better than him.

368
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:22,100
He's just an investigator
in a movie.

369
00:24:22,233 --> 00:24:24,433
You, in real life.

370
00:24:25,967 --> 00:24:27,500
Oh, go ahead and rest.

371
00:24:27,633 --> 00:24:29,200
Just remember.

372
00:24:29,367 --> 00:24:31,167
The grandchild who is beautiful,

373
00:24:31,467 --> 00:24:33,300
inherited her beauty from
grandmother.

374
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:03,000
Hi, Dear.

375
00:25:03,133 --> 00:25:04,200
Good morning!

376
00:25:04,333 --> 00:25:05,733
Good morning, Grandmother.

377
00:25:05,867 --> 00:25:07,867
Oh, why are you wearing this?

378
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:10,567
Of course, zumba!

379
00:25:10,700 --> 00:25:11,933
And you're coming with me.

380
00:25:12,067 --> 00:25:13,733
Let's do zumba.

381
00:25:13,867 --> 00:25:15,867
Aren't you off today?

382
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:17,600
Oh, Grandmother, it's my off

383
00:25:17,733 --> 00:25:19,400
but godmother is on duty,

384
00:25:19,533 --> 00:25:20,800
so I'll just accompany with her.

385
00:25:20,933 --> 00:25:22,267
Oh, okay.

386
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:25,033
Oh, come on, breakfast
was ready a while ago.

387
00:25:25,167 --> 00:25:26,200
- Ah, okay, okay.
- Come on..

388
00:25:26,333 --> 00:25:28,600
Before that,
let's take a selfie.

389
00:25:28,733 --> 00:25:30,767
- Grandmother, I just woke up.
- Of course.

390
00:25:30,900 --> 00:25:32,033
Oh, you just woke up?

391
00:25:32,167 --> 00:25:34,100
That's okay.
That's how we are.

392
00:25:34,233 --> 00:25:36,767
As long as we wake up fresh,
we'll be beautiful

393
00:25:36,933 --> 00:25:38,600
because that's our race.

394
00:25:38,733 --> 00:25:40,367
Okay. All right.

395
00:25:40,500 --> 00:25:41,067
- Okay.
- Okay.

396
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:43,833
#WokeUpLikeThis.

397
00:25:45,733 --> 00:25:47,100
Yes!

398
00:25:47,233 --> 00:25:48,633
- All right. Let's go.
- All right.

399
00:25:48,767 --> 00:25:50,600
Oh, okay, I'll go ahead outside?

400
00:25:50,733 --> 00:25:51,667
- Just go with it?
- Oh, okay, Grandmother.

401
00:25:51,800 --> 00:25:53,233
Okay.

402
00:26:06,433 --> 00:26:08,333
That smells good.

403
00:26:08,500 --> 00:26:09,567
Hey, I just remembered.

404
00:26:09,700 --> 00:26:10,633
Yes?

405
00:26:10,767 --> 00:26:11,933
Later, I'll pick you up
from the bank, huh?

406
00:26:12,067 --> 00:26:14,267
Why? Can you come home early?

407
00:26:14,400 --> 00:26:18,100
For you, I'll go home early.

408
00:26:18,667 --> 00:26:21,500
You really are something else,
you don't run out of answers.

409
00:26:21,633 --> 00:26:22,967
But okay, if...

410
00:26:23,100 --> 00:26:26,233
you finish early later
pick me up

411
00:26:26,833 --> 00:26:28,433
then...

412
00:26:28,967 --> 00:26:30,067
let's go out?

413
00:26:30,200 --> 00:26:31,900
Are you inviting me out?

414
00:26:32,033 --> 00:26:32,933
Yes.

415
00:26:33,067 --> 00:26:34,833
Is it our anniversary?

416
00:26:35,533 --> 00:26:36,967
Not really.

417
00:26:37,433 --> 00:26:38,600
What's the occassion?

418
00:26:38,733 --> 00:26:40,600
Well...

419
00:26:40,733 --> 00:26:42,100
I'll tell you later.

420
00:26:42,267 --> 00:26:43,500
I'll just get the rice, okay?

421
00:26:43,633 --> 00:26:45,467
Later...

422
00:26:50,233 --> 00:26:51,767
Here.

423
00:26:53,467 --> 00:26:55,467
What is it?

424
00:26:55,600 --> 00:26:57,067
Can just tell me now?

425
00:26:57,200 --> 00:26:59,600
You know I don't like
surprises, right?

426
00:27:00,333 --> 00:27:01,300
You're so stubborn.

427
00:27:01,433 --> 00:27:03,900
I said later,

428
00:27:04,567 --> 00:27:06,300
besides,

429
00:27:06,433 --> 00:27:07,833
I don't know if you'll like

430
00:27:07,967 --> 00:27:10,100
what I'm going to say or not.

431
00:27:10,233 --> 00:27:11,567
Come on...

432
00:27:12,233 --> 00:27:14,000
What's that?

433
00:27:14,133 --> 00:27:15,800
Tell me.
What is it? What is it?

434
00:27:15,967 --> 00:27:17,733
You are so stubborn.

435
00:27:17,867 --> 00:27:19,667
If you nag at me,

436
00:27:19,800 --> 00:27:22,200
I won't sleep by your side
later.

437
00:27:22,333 --> 00:27:23,767
Do you like that?

438
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:27,533
Oh, okay.

439
00:27:27,667 --> 00:27:31,600
I'll agree, but can we just
eat here?

440
00:27:31,733 --> 00:27:33,233
Because...

441
00:27:34,467 --> 00:27:36,433
I'll also tell you something.

442
00:27:36,567 --> 00:27:37,900
What?

443
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:40,667
What

444
00:27:42,500 --> 00:27:43,600
What is it?

445
00:27:43,733 --> 00:27:46,333
Oh, come on, tell me...

446
00:27:46,467 --> 00:27:48,933
- Hey, tell me...
- Don't be stubborn.

447
00:27:49,100 --> 00:27:50,567
I won't sleep with you later.

448
00:27:50,700 --> 00:27:52,300
Okay.

449
00:27:52,433 --> 00:27:54,367
- Okay.
- Do you want that?

450
00:27:54,500 --> 00:27:55,867
- No. Oh, okay.
- You don't want to.

451
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:58,567
- You eat first.
- Don't be stubborn.

452
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:01,100
Eat now, hurry.
You'll be late.

453
00:28:01,233 --> 00:28:02,933
- Morning, Boss!
- Morning!

454
00:28:03,067 --> 00:28:04,400
- Morning.
- Morning.

455
00:28:04,533 --> 00:28:06,033
Is it still morning?

456
00:28:06,167 --> 00:28:07,233
Why are you late?

457
00:28:07,367 --> 00:28:09,267
Because of the heavy traffic.

458
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:10,967
We're complete, Boss.

459
00:28:11,100 --> 00:28:11,900
Good, good.

460
00:28:12,033 --> 00:28:14,000
To be sure you won't fail
anymore.

461
00:28:14,133 --> 00:28:15,533
What did you say?

462
00:28:17,533 --> 00:28:19,433
My last transaction
was not a failure!

463
00:28:19,967 --> 00:28:20,900
Really?

464
00:28:21,033 --> 00:28:22,067
I must have heard differently.

465
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:23,833
Wait, wait, wait.

466
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:25,667
Do that later.

467
00:28:25,800 --> 00:28:26,633
Have you had your coffee yet?

468
00:28:26,767 --> 00:28:28,500
Well, you're stronger
than my coffee...

469
00:28:28,633 --> 00:28:29,667
That's enough.

470
00:28:29,800 --> 00:28:32,033
First, go to the Rural Bank
in San Isidro.

471
00:28:32,167 --> 00:28:33,900
Today is payday.

472
00:28:34,500 --> 00:28:36,900
We'll withdraw a lot.

473
00:28:45,367 --> 00:28:47,233
- Bobby!
- Hey.

474
00:28:47,667 --> 00:28:48,467
- Oh, Bobby.
- Hello.

475
00:28:48,600 --> 00:28:50,500
- My Godchild.
- Have you had lunch yet?

476
00:28:50,633 --> 00:28:52,267
- Why don't you eat here?
- I've eaten already.

477
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:54,067
- Too bad.
- Godmother,

478
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:55,033
aren't you going to work today?

479
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:57,067
I was supposed
to go with you on duty.

480
00:28:57,200 --> 00:28:59,333
Karlo doesn't want me
to report for work.

481
00:28:59,467 --> 00:29:02,133
He heard about
what happened last night.

482
00:29:03,533 --> 00:29:05,567
I'm letting your godmother
rest for now.

483
00:29:06,267 --> 00:29:09,500
Besides, her early retirement
is coming soon.

484
00:29:09,633 --> 00:29:11,167
Is it hard to go to war.

485
00:29:11,300 --> 00:29:14,367
Bobby, enjoy your time off.

486
00:29:14,500 --> 00:29:17,700
Dear, take a break sometimes.

487
00:29:17,833 --> 00:29:19,367
Okay, I'll date Grandmother now.

488
00:29:19,500 --> 00:29:21,033
For sure, she'll be happy.

489
00:29:21,167 --> 00:29:22,867
Okay, I'll go ahead.

490
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:25,533
- Bye, Bobby.
- Bye.

491
00:29:26,200 --> 00:29:27,567
- Be careful, okay?
- Yes.

492
00:29:30,367 --> 00:29:31,600
Be careful.

493
00:29:31,733 --> 00:29:33,500
Okay.

494
00:29:38,833 --> 00:29:39,900
<i> El Hepe!</i>

495
00:29:40,033 --> 00:29:41,300
<i> You're finished!</i>

496
00:29:48,433 --> 00:29:49,633
<i> My law...</i>

497
00:29:49,767 --> 00:29:51,600
<i>- will finish you off.
- Will finish you off.</i>

498
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:55,267
No, no...

499
00:29:56,200 --> 00:29:57,000
Mayor!

500
00:29:57,133 --> 00:29:58,267
Oh?

501
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:17,800
Mayor, Major Flores
is already in the office.

502
00:30:18,867 --> 00:30:20,467
Let's go.

503
00:30:29,933 --> 00:30:31,000
Oh, morning.

504
00:30:31,133 --> 00:30:32,367
Good morning, Ma'am.

505
00:30:32,500 --> 00:30:34,333
I'll leave this with you for
now.

506
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:36,633
Just get it from me later,
Ma'am.

507
00:30:36,767 --> 00:30:38,800
Okay, no problem.

508
00:30:46,400 --> 00:30:47,667
Do you know...

509
00:30:47,800 --> 00:30:49,933
I took a pregnancy test twice.

510
00:30:50,067 --> 00:30:51,667
- Oh.
- Both were positive!

511
00:30:51,800 --> 00:30:53,567
Really?
Congrats!

512
00:30:53,700 --> 00:30:54,900
Thank you.

513
00:30:55,033 --> 00:30:56,333
Congratulations.

514
00:30:58,400 --> 00:31:00,133
Oh, sorry. Just gossipmonger.

515
00:31:00,267 --> 00:31:01,467
No, it's okay.

516
00:31:01,600 --> 00:31:03,400
I'm so talkative during work
hours.

517
00:31:03,533 --> 00:31:04,833
What transaction, Miss?

518
00:31:04,967 --> 00:31:07,633
I'll just deposit this and then
please update my account

519
00:31:07,767 --> 00:31:10,000
because I'm going
to date my grandmother.

520
00:31:10,667 --> 00:31:12,800
Sorry, I'm talkative too.

521
00:31:12,933 --> 00:31:14,833
We're the same.

522
00:31:16,400 --> 00:31:20,467
Oh, do you know of a restaurant
that's cheap but delicious?

523
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:23,200
Because my boyfriend and I are
going on a date later.

524
00:31:23,333 --> 00:31:27,367
I was going to tell him that
we're going to have a baby.

525
00:31:27,500 --> 00:31:29,367
Oh, that's so fun.

526
00:31:29,500 --> 00:31:31,700
I'm sure your boyfriend
will be happy.

527
00:31:32,167 --> 00:31:33,533
I hope so.

528
00:31:33,667 --> 00:31:35,933
Well, this wasn't planned.

529
00:31:36,067 --> 00:31:39,000
So I don't know if he'll be
happy or not.

530
00:31:40,233 --> 00:31:42,100
If he's not happy,

531
00:31:42,267 --> 00:31:43,500
tell me.

532
00:31:43,633 --> 00:31:45,367
I'll send him to jail.

533
00:31:45,500 --> 00:31:47,167
- I'm a police officer.
- What?

534
00:31:47,667 --> 00:31:49,533
- You're the same.
- Really?

535
00:31:49,933 --> 00:31:51,400
Oh, wait, I'm just
going to text someone.

536
00:31:51,533 --> 00:31:53,800
Oh, okay.
I'll take care of this.

537
00:31:56,267 --> 00:31:57,233
Bro, I'll just go
to the comfort room.

538
00:31:57,367 --> 00:31:58,033
Oh, okay, okay.

539
00:31:58,933 --> 00:32:01,300
- Oh.
- Thank you.

540
00:32:16,167 --> 00:32:19,000
Lieutenant Conde,
congratulations

541
00:32:19,133 --> 00:32:20,900
on your successful operation.

542
00:32:21,133 --> 00:32:22,900
Thank you very much, Mayor.

543
00:32:26,633 --> 00:32:28,967
Bro, congratulations.

544
00:32:29,100 --> 00:32:31,500
Oh, Lieutenant Garcia,

545
00:32:31,633 --> 00:32:33,467
I'm Conde's partner.

546
00:32:33,600 --> 00:32:35,133
It was a team effort.

547
00:32:35,267 --> 00:32:37,000
- Oh, okay.
- Mayor, Mayor!

548
00:32:37,133 --> 00:32:39,433
What is your reaction to the
recent announcement

549
00:32:39,567 --> 00:32:41,700
of action star
Mr. Victor Santiago

550
00:32:41,833 --> 00:32:44,467
as your opponent
in the upcoming elections?

551
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:46,567
We are in a democracy.

552
00:32:46,700 --> 00:32:50,167
You can run
as long as you are qualified.

553
00:32:50,900 --> 00:32:53,733
Sir, I was going to ask you
for a favor.

554
00:32:54,200 --> 00:32:55,667
What is that, Conde?

555
00:32:55,800 --> 00:32:58,133
Maybe I can take a leave of
absence, even for just a week.

556
00:32:58,267 --> 00:33:00,100
Why? Are you and Lara
having a problem?

557
00:33:00,233 --> 00:33:01,433
She hasn't said anything yet,

558
00:33:01,567 --> 00:33:04,500
but based on what I've observed
these past few days,

559
00:33:04,633 --> 00:33:06,067
it looks like...

560
00:33:06,500 --> 00:33:08,167
we're going to have a baby.

561
00:33:08,800 --> 00:33:09,733
Lara is pregnant?!

562
00:33:09,867 --> 00:33:11,733
Congratulations!

563
00:33:12,167 --> 00:33:14,200
I hope so, I hope so, I hope so.

564
00:33:23,867 --> 00:33:24,967
Hello, Bobby?

565
00:33:25,100 --> 00:33:28,200
Didn't I tell you
to take a break?

566
00:33:28,833 --> 00:33:30,267
Godmother...

567
00:33:30,667 --> 00:33:32,900
I'm here at the
Rural Bank of San Isidro.

568
00:33:34,233 --> 00:33:35,667
It looks like this bank
is going to be robbed.

569
00:33:35,800 --> 00:33:36,733
What?

570
00:33:36,867 --> 00:33:39,167
Don't be a hero, Bobby.

571
00:33:40,833 --> 00:33:42,300
Hello, Bobby?

572
00:33:42,967 --> 00:33:44,533
Hello?

573
00:33:46,667 --> 00:33:48,933
Mister, where's the key to the
locker?

574
00:33:49,067 --> 00:33:51,400
It's with my companion,
in the comfort room.

575
00:33:54,100 --> 00:33:55,667
Mister...

576
00:33:58,000 --> 00:33:59,567
Hurry!

577
00:34:00,467 --> 00:34:02,700
Mister, give me the key, please.

578
00:34:08,200 --> 00:34:11,233
Good morning, guys!

579
00:34:11,933 --> 00:34:14,533
No one will die

580
00:34:14,667 --> 00:34:17,000
if no one is stubborn.

581
00:34:17,133 --> 00:34:21,700
We just need money!

582
00:34:23,300 --> 00:34:27,033
To you criminals, ruthless
people like you,

583
00:34:27,167 --> 00:34:29,800
you will taste
the fist of El Hepe.

584
00:34:29,967 --> 00:34:32,833
Calabari needs
a change of leadership.

585
00:34:32,967 --> 00:34:34,433
- For Calabari!
- Yes!

586
00:34:35,967 --> 00:34:40,367
- What are you doing?
- It's better not to take action

587
00:34:40,500 --> 00:34:42,367
because the elections are near.

588
00:34:42,500 --> 00:34:43,567
Boss, what now?

589
00:34:43,700 --> 00:34:44,900
Boss, set us free.

590
00:34:45,033 --> 00:34:46,267
Who arrested you?

591
00:34:46,400 --> 00:34:47,400
There, there, Boss!
She's the one!

592
00:34:47,533 --> 00:34:48,900
There, there, there.

593
00:34:49,033 --> 00:34:50,933
Sergeant Enriquez, good morning!

594
00:34:51,067 --> 00:34:54,400
I know you have a personal
involvement in the case.

595
00:34:54,533 --> 00:34:56,567
That's why I'm the best person
for the job, Sir,

596
00:34:56,700 --> 00:34:57,533
because I will do everything,

597
00:34:57,667 --> 00:34:58,900
just to solve this case.

598
00:34:59,033 --> 00:35:02,467
If you want to be
the girlfriend of the leader

599
00:35:02,600 --> 00:35:04,300
of the investigation group,

600
00:35:04,467 --> 00:35:06,167
we can talk about it.

601
00:35:08,033 --> 00:35:09,733
She's busy with something else.

602
00:35:09,867 --> 00:35:11,733
Don't insult me at work

603
00:35:11,867 --> 00:35:13,700
because I love being a cop.

604
00:35:13,833 --> 00:35:15,233
Put your hands up!

605
00:35:16,400 --> 00:35:18,233
That's four, okay?
Three for me, one for you.

606
00:35:18,367 --> 00:35:20,667
I can handle it. Two for you and
two for me too.

607
00:35:20,800 --> 00:35:22,900
Tonyo looks like
he's going to go at it tonight.

608
00:35:23,033 --> 00:35:25,000
Enriquez? What are you doing?
